### 3.4 Accessibility Violations

| Issue | Location | Severity |
|-------|----------|----------|
| **Range input invisible** | [CausalNode.tsx](file:///d:/Projects/CURRENT/DigitalTwin/digital-twin-frontend/src/components/nodes/CausalNode.tsx) line 77: `opacity-0` on `<input type="range">` | 🔴 Screen readers may find it but it has no label, no `aria-label`, no `aria-valuemin/max/now`. |
| **No `<label>` elements** | PolicySimulator textarea, all `<select>` elements, HealthChat input, CausalGraph textarea | 🔴 None of the form inputs have associated `<label>` or `aria-label`. |
| **Emoji as icon** | AQIMaps (🗺️), EmissionMaps (🌡️, 🏭), SectorMaps (📊), PolicySimulator (💰, 📈, etc.) | 🟡 Emojis are used as functional icons. They have `role="img"` on some (AQIMaps, EmissionMaps) but NOT on SectorMaps or PolicySimulator emojis. |
| **Color-only information** | ImpactPanel — reduction vs. increase solely by green vs. red text. No icon/text indicator. | 🔴 Fails WCAG 1.4.1 (Use of Color). |
| **No skip navigation** | [layout.tsx](file:///d:/Projects/CURRENT/DigitalTwin/digital-twin-frontend/app/layout.tsx) | 🟡 No skip-to-content link. |
| **Interactive elements lack focus styles** | All custom buttons using glass-panel/btn-primary patterns — some have `:hover` but no `:focus-visible` | 🔴 Keyboard users cannot see which element is focused. |
| **Modal trap** | [ImpactModal](file:///d:/Projects/CURRENT/DigitalTwin/digital-twin-frontend/src/components/SolutionsCatalog.tsx#193-267) in SolutionsCatalog: no focus trap, no `Escape` key handler | 🔴 Modal does not trap focus. |
| **No [alt](file:///d:/Projects/CURRENT/DigitalTwin/digital-twin-frontend/src/components/HealthChat.tsx#14-145) text issues** | Map images use generic alt text like "AQI Heatmap" | 🟡 Acceptable but not descriptive of content. |
| **Mobile navigation** | Navigation has no hamburger/mobile menu | 🔴 Desktop-only nav with no responsive behavior. Links will overflow/squeeze on mobile. |
| **No `aria-live` region** | LiveAQI live data, chat messages, simulation results | 🟡 Dynamic content updates not announced to screen readers. |

### 3.5 Prop Inconsistencies

| Pattern | Issue |
|---------|-------|
| `aqiData: any` | Used in [HealthImpact](file:///d:/Projects/CURRENT/DigitalTwin/digital-twin-frontend/src/components/HealthImpact.tsx#10-171) and [HealthChat](file:///d:/Projects/CURRENT/DigitalTwin/digital-twin-frontend/src/components/HealthChat.tsx#14-145) — should use the [AQIData](file:///d:/Projects/CURRENT/DigitalTwin/digital-twin-frontend/src/components/LiveAQI.tsx#6-18) interface from GlobalStateContext |
| `onAqiUpdate` callback unused | [LiveAQI](file:///d:/Projects/CURRENT/DigitalTwin/digital-twin-frontend/src/components/LiveAQI.tsx#19-102) accepts it but [AQIHealthImpact](file:///d:/Projects/CURRENT/DigitalTwin/digital-twin-frontend/src/components/AQIHealthImpact.tsx#119-312) invokes `<LiveAQI />` without it. The callback pattern is leftover dead API. |
| `data.onChange` mutation | [CausalNode](file:///d:/Projects/CURRENT/DigitalTwin/digital-twin-frontend/src/components/nodes/CausalNode.tsx#13-102) directly mutates `data.onChange` — React anti-pattern (should be via parent state update) |

### 3.6 Direct DOM Manipulation

| File | Lines | Issue |
|------|-------|-------|
| [AQIMaps.tsx](file:///d:/Projects/CURRENT/DigitalTwin/digital-twin-frontend/src/components/AQIMaps.tsx) | 20-28, 41-44 | `document.getElementById()` + direct `.src` manipulation. **Anti-React pattern.** |
| [EmissionMaps.tsx](file:///d:/Projects/CURRENT/DigitalTwin/digital-twin-frontend/src/components/EmissionMaps.tsx) | 19-27, 40-43 | Same pattern. |
| [SectorMaps.tsx](file:///d:/Projects/CURRENT/DigitalTwin/digital-twin-frontend/src/components/SectorMaps.tsx) | 28-37, 44-48 | Same pattern. |

> [!CAUTION]
> All 3 map components bypass React's rendering to manually set `<img>` `src` via `document.getElementById()`. This defeats React's reconciliation and can cause stale state.

